WEBVTT

00:00:00.506 --> 00:00:04.500 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:00:07.356 --> 00:00:08.586 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Welcome to our session on

00:00:08.586 --> 00:00:09.586 A:middle
Universal Links.

00:00:10.096 --> 00:00:11.946 A:middle
My name is Jonathan Grynspan and

00:00:11.946 --> 00:00:13.146 A:middle
I work on the Core Frameworks

00:00:13.146 --> 00:00:13.876 A:middle
Team at Apple.

00:00:14.966 --> 00:00:16.556 A:middle
Today, I'll be showing you how

00:00:16.556 --> 00:00:18.116 A:middle
to use universal links in your

00:00:18.116 --> 00:00:18.366 A:middle
app.

00:00:19.246 --> 00:00:20.426 A:middle
We introduced the universal

00:00:20.426 --> 00:00:22.566 A:middle
links in iOS 9 as a great way to

00:00:22.566 --> 00:00:24.436 A:middle
provide rich content both on the

00:00:24.436 --> 00:00:25.506 A:middle
web and in your app.

00:00:26.496 --> 00:00:27.986 A:middle
Today, I'll be showing you the

00:00:27.986 --> 00:00:29.196 A:middle
enhancements we've made to this

00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:29.586 A:middle
feature.

00:00:30.436 --> 00:00:31.676 A:middle
Whether you've already adopted

00:00:31.676 --> 00:00:33.306 A:middle
universal links in your iOS app

00:00:33.606 --> 00:00:34.846 A:middle
or you're adding them to your

00:00:34.846 --> 00:00:36.676 A:middle
macOS app, you will want to pay

00:00:36.676 --> 00:00:37.936 A:middle
close attention to the changes

00:00:37.936 --> 00:00:38.726 A:middle
I'll be discussing.

00:00:40.436 --> 00:00:42.466 A:middle
To begin, let's talk about what

00:00:42.466 --> 00:00:43.626 A:middle
universal links are.

00:00:45.566 --> 00:00:47.966 A:middle
Universal links are HTTP or

00:00:47.966 --> 00:00:50.606 A:middle
HTTPS URLs that Apple's

00:00:50.606 --> 00:00:52.516 A:middle
operating systems recognize as

00:00:52.516 --> 00:00:54.146 A:middle
pointing to resources either on

00:00:54.146 --> 00:00:55.876 A:middle
the web or in your app.

00:00:56.756 --> 00:00:58.616 A:middle
This means that a single URL can

00:00:58.616 --> 00:01:00.166 A:middle
represent that content, whether

00:00:58.616 --> 00:01:00.166 A:middle
represent that content, whether

00:01:00.166 --> 00:01:01.246 A:middle
your users have your app

00:01:01.246 --> 00:01:03.056 A:middle
installed or it just haven't

00:01:03.056 --> 00:01:03.876 A:middle
downloaded it yet.

00:01:04.575 --> 00:01:05.816 A:middle
They are great way to increase

00:01:05.816 --> 00:01:07.216 A:middle
user engagement within your app.

00:01:08.396 --> 00:01:09.896 A:middle
Universal links are introduced

00:01:09.896 --> 00:01:11.926 A:middle
in iOS 9 and tvOS 10.

00:01:12.346 --> 00:01:13.936 A:middle
I'm happy to announce that we

00:01:13.936 --> 00:01:15.256 A:middle
are introducing them to the Mac

00:01:15.256 --> 00:01:17.796 A:middle
with macOS 10.15, whether you're

00:01:17.796 --> 00:01:19.676 A:middle
using AppKit or UIKit.

00:01:20.026 --> 00:01:21.756 A:middle
I'll tell you more about that in

00:01:21.756 --> 00:01:22.176 A:middle
a moment.

00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:24.666 A:middle
Universal links are securely

00:01:24.666 --> 00:01:26.406 A:middle
associated between your app and

00:01:26.406 --> 00:01:27.096 A:middle
your website.

00:01:27.836 --> 00:01:29.236 A:middle
Your app adopts an entitlement

00:01:29.236 --> 00:01:30.936 A:middle
in Xcode that indicates which

00:01:30.936 --> 00:01:32.926 A:middle
domains it can represent and

00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:34.436 A:middle
your web server adopts a single

00:01:34.436 --> 00:01:36.016 A:middle
JSON file that contains more

00:01:36.016 --> 00:01:37.806 A:middle
details about what parts of its

00:01:37.806 --> 00:01:39.506 A:middle
domain are representable in your

00:01:39.506 --> 00:01:39.746 A:middle
app.

00:01:40.596 --> 00:01:42.226 A:middle
These two ways secure handshake

00:01:42.226 --> 00:01:43.866 A:middle
ensures nobody can redirect your

00:01:43.866 --> 00:01:45.526 A:middle
users into their apps instead of

00:01:45.526 --> 00:01:46.026 A:middle
yours.

00:01:47.536 --> 00:01:48.916 A:middle
We recommend that where you are

00:01:48.916 --> 00:01:50.436 A:middle
currently using custom URL

00:01:50.436 --> 00:01:52.326 A:middle
schemes, you begin migrating to

00:01:52.326 --> 00:01:53.486 A:middle
universal links today.

00:01:54.306 --> 00:01:55.606 A:middle
Custom URL schemes are

00:01:55.606 --> 00:01:57.656 A:middle
inherently insecure and can be

00:01:57.656 --> 00:01:59.186 A:middle
abused by malicious developers.

00:01:59.726 --> 00:02:01.626 A:middle
New uses of custom URL schemes

00:01:59.726 --> 00:02:01.626 A:middle
New uses of custom URL schemes

00:02:01.626 --> 00:02:02.746 A:middle
are highly discouraged.

00:02:05.106 --> 00:02:06.626 A:middle
Now that we know what universal

00:02:06.626 --> 00:02:08.515 A:middle
links are, let's talk about how

00:02:08.515 --> 00:02:09.205 A:middle
to build them.

00:02:09.645 --> 00:02:10.596 A:middle
We'll start with your web

00:02:10.596 --> 00:02:10.996 A:middle
server.

00:02:12.816 --> 00:02:14.606 A:middle
Your web server must have a

00:02:14.606 --> 00:02:17.016 A:middle
valid HTTPS certificate.

00:02:17.526 --> 00:02:19.886 A:middle
HTTP is not secure and cannot be

00:02:19.886 --> 00:02:21.646 A:middle
used to validate an association

00:02:21.806 --> 00:02:23.026 A:middle
between your app and your

00:02:23.026 --> 00:02:23.546 A:middle
website.

00:02:23.846 --> 00:02:25.936 A:middle
The root certificate used to

00:02:25.936 --> 00:02:28.226 A:middle
sign your HTTPS certificate must

00:02:28.226 --> 00:02:29.626 A:middle
be recognized by the operating

00:02:29.626 --> 00:02:30.126 A:middle
system.

00:02:30.646 --> 00:02:32.126 A:middle
Custom root certificates are not

00:02:32.126 --> 00:02:32.606 A:middle
supported.

00:02:33.816 --> 00:02:34.986 A:middle
After generating your

00:02:34.986 --> 00:02:36.366 A:middle
certificate and configuring your

00:02:36.366 --> 00:02:37.596 A:middle
server, add your

00:02:37.596 --> 00:02:39.636 A:middle
apple-app-site-association file.

00:02:40.226 --> 00:02:41.586 A:middle
This is a JSON file.

00:02:41.586 --> 00:02:42.776 A:middle
We'll discuss this format in a

00:02:42.776 --> 00:02:43.206 A:middle
moment.

00:02:43.556 --> 00:02:45.446 A:middle
When your app is installed on an

00:02:45.446 --> 00:02:46.896 A:middle
Apple device, the operating

00:02:46.896 --> 00:02:48.326 A:middle
system downloads this file to

00:02:48.326 --> 00:02:49.916 A:middle
determine what services the

00:02:49.916 --> 00:02:51.306 A:middle
server will let your app use.

00:02:51.616 --> 00:02:53.666 A:middle
The system also periodically

00:02:53.666 --> 00:02:55.496 A:middle
downloads updates for this file.

00:02:56.246 --> 00:02:57.626 A:middle
Universal links are one of many

00:02:57.626 --> 00:02:59.086 A:middle
services that may be included in

00:02:59.086 --> 00:02:59.606 A:middle
this file.

00:03:00.606 --> 00:03:02.376 A:middle
This file should be located at

00:03:02.506 --> 00:03:06.126 A:middle
HTTPS://your domain name/

00:03:07.286 --> 00:03:10.216 A:middle
.well-known/apple-app-site-

00:03:10.216 --> 00:03:11.036 A:middle
association.

00:03:11.956 --> 00:03:13.346 A:middle
Other paths are deprecated.

00:03:14.226 --> 00:03:15.566 A:middle
In the past, we've discussed

00:03:15.566 --> 00:03:16.056 A:middle
signing your

00:03:16.056 --> 00:03:17.816 A:middle
apple-app-site-association file.

00:03:18.356 --> 00:03:19.666 A:middle
This has never been a necessary

00:03:19.666 --> 00:03:21.376 A:middle
step to support universal links

00:03:21.416 --> 00:03:22.696 A:middle
so it is now deprecated.

00:03:23.926 --> 00:03:25.936 A:middle
Support for sign JSON files and

00:03:25.936 --> 00:03:27.606 A:middle
JSON files at other paths will

00:03:27.606 --> 00:03:29.156 A:middle
be removed in a future release.

00:03:29.446 --> 00:03:32.676 A:middle
With that out of the way, let's

00:03:32.676 --> 00:03:33.426 A:middle
take a look at your

00:03:33.426 --> 00:03:35.316 A:middle
apple-app-site-association file.

00:03:36.156 --> 00:03:37.336 A:middle
If you already have one of these

00:03:37.336 --> 00:03:38.776 A:middle
files on your web server this

00:03:38.776 --> 00:03:41.336 A:middle
probably looks familiar, but we

00:03:41.336 --> 00:03:42.786 A:middle
have a few changes to introduce

00:03:42.786 --> 00:03:42.996 A:middle
today.

00:03:43.686 --> 00:03:45.556 A:middle
At the top level is a dictionary

00:03:45.556 --> 00:03:47.036 A:middle
whose keys are service types.

00:03:47.036 --> 00:03:48.976 A:middle
For universal links, the key is

00:03:48.976 --> 00:03:50.896 A:middle
applinks like you see here but

00:03:50.896 --> 00:03:52.316 A:middle
other services are also

00:03:52.316 --> 00:03:52.766 A:middle
available.

00:03:53.586 --> 00:03:54.966 A:middle
We'll be focusing solely on

00:03:54.966 --> 00:03:55.886 A:middle
Universal Links.

00:03:56.316 --> 00:03:58.336 A:middle
Under that top level key are the

00:03:58.336 --> 00:03:59.976 A:middle
apps key and the details key.

00:04:00.576 --> 00:04:02.276 A:middle
If you are targeting iOS 13,

00:04:02.606 --> 00:04:05.926 A:middle
tvOS 13 and macOS 10.15, you do

00:04:05.926 --> 00:04:07.636 A:middle
not need the apps key, so you

00:04:07.636 --> 00:04:08.266 A:middle
can remove it.

00:04:09.066 --> 00:04:10.376 A:middle
If you are continuing to provide

00:04:10.376 --> 00:04:12.956 A:middle
support for iOS 12, tvOS 12 or

00:04:12.956 --> 00:04:14.526 A:middle
earlier, you'll still need it.

00:04:14.816 --> 00:04:16.125 A:middle
For universal links, it should

00:04:16.125 --> 00:04:17.456 A:middle
always be an empty array.

00:04:18.846 --> 00:04:20.146 A:middle
The details key contains an

00:04:20.146 --> 00:04:21.736 A:middle
array of dictionaries, each of

00:04:21.736 --> 00:04:23.416 A:middle
which represents a specific apps

00:04:23.416 --> 00:04:24.926 A:middle
universal links configuration.

00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:27.326 A:middle
In the past, we supported using

00:04:27.326 --> 00:04:28.596 A:middle
a dictionary structure here

00:04:28.626 --> 00:04:30.126 A:middle
instead of an array but that

00:04:30.126 --> 00:04:31.626 A:middle
configuration is obsolete.

00:04:33.136 --> 00:04:34.536 A:middle
Under the details key is an

00:04:34.536 --> 00:04:36.556 A:middle
appID key whose value is your

00:04:36.556 --> 00:04:37.346 A:middle
app identifier.

00:04:38.006 --> 00:04:39.676 A:middle
Your app identifier consists of

00:04:39.676 --> 00:04:41.196 A:middle
an alphanumeric, 10 character

00:04:41.196 --> 00:04:43.316 A:middle
prefix provided by Apple, a

00:04:43.316 --> 00:04:44.996 A:middle
period, and your bundle

00:04:44.996 --> 00:04:45.516 A:middle
identifier.

00:04:46.936 --> 00:04:48.536 A:middle
The prefix may or may not be

00:04:48.536 --> 00:04:49.876 A:middle
equal to your team identifier.

00:04:50.146 --> 00:04:51.486 A:middle
Check the developer portal to

00:04:51.486 --> 00:04:52.776 A:middle
confirm your app identifier.

00:04:52.776 --> 00:04:55.086 A:middle
If you have multiple apps with

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.296 A:middle
the same universal links

00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:58.316 A:middle
configuration, you may not want

00:04:58.316 --> 00:04:59.726 A:middle
to repeat the relevant JSON.

00:05:00.056 --> 00:05:01.776 A:middle
If you are targeting this year's

00:05:01.776 --> 00:05:03.296 A:middle
releases, you can reduce the

00:05:03.296 --> 00:05:04.926 A:middle
size of this file by using the

00:05:04.926 --> 00:05:06.226 A:middle
plural appIDs key.

00:05:06.656 --> 00:05:08.316 A:middle
The value of that key is an

00:05:08.316 --> 00:05:09.816 A:middle
array of app identifiers.

00:05:10.486 --> 00:05:11.906 A:middle
If you need to support previous

00:05:11.906 --> 00:05:13.466 A:middle
releases, you should keep using

00:05:13.466 --> 00:05:15.346 A:middle
the singular appID key for each

00:05:15.346 --> 00:05:15.606 A:middle
app.

00:05:16.646 --> 00:05:17.826 A:middle
Next is the paths key.

00:05:18.326 --> 00:05:19.736 A:middle
This key contains an array of

00:05:19.736 --> 00:05:20.526 A:middle
path patterns.

00:05:20.586 --> 00:05:22.246 A:middle
Pattern matching is performed

00:05:22.246 --> 00:05:23.566 A:middle
the same way it is in terminal.

00:05:24.026 --> 00:05:25.676 A:middle
The asterisk is used to indicate

00:05:25.676 --> 00:05:27.216 A:middle
multiple wildcard characters

00:05:27.216 --> 00:05:28.696 A:middle
while the question mark matches

00:05:28.696 --> 00:05:29.666 A:middle
just one character.

00:05:30.636 --> 00:05:31.856 A:middle
Beginning this year, we are

00:05:31.856 --> 00:05:33.486 A:middle
replacing the paths key with the

00:05:33.486 --> 00:05:34.266 A:middle
components key.

00:05:35.346 --> 00:05:36.966 A:middle
This key's value is an array of

00:05:36.966 --> 00:05:38.366 A:middle
dictionaries, each of which

00:05:38.366 --> 00:05:40.066 A:middle
contains zero or more URL

00:05:40.066 --> 00:05:41.526 A:middle
components to pattern match

00:05:41.526 --> 00:05:42.046 A:middle
against.

00:05:42.396 --> 00:05:44.546 A:middle
As before, you can match against

00:05:44.546 --> 00:05:45.936 A:middle
the URL's path component whose

00:05:45.936 --> 00:05:47.116 A:middle
key is the forward slash.

00:05:47.486 --> 00:05:49.446 A:middle
If you need to support previous

00:05:49.446 --> 00:05:50.986 A:middle
releases, you can keep the paths

00:05:50.986 --> 00:05:51.206 A:middle
key.

00:05:52.026 --> 00:05:55.766 A:middle
iOS 13, tvOS 13 and macOS 10.15

00:05:55.766 --> 00:05:57.296 A:middle
will ignore it if the components

00:05:57.296 --> 00:05:58.016 A:middle
key is present.

00:05:58.556 --> 00:06:00.346 A:middle
And now you can match against

00:05:58.556 --> 00:06:00.346 A:middle
And now you can match against

00:06:00.346 --> 00:06:01.596 A:middle
the URL's fragment component

00:06:01.956 --> 00:06:03.646 A:middle
whose key is the hash mark and

00:06:03.646 --> 00:06:04.436 A:middle
you can match the query

00:06:04.436 --> 00:06:05.566 A:middle
component whose key is the

00:06:05.566 --> 00:06:06.236 A:middle
question mark.

00:06:07.076 --> 00:06:09.466 A:middle
Now many, if not most URLs out

00:06:09.466 --> 00:06:10.616 A:middle
there divide their query

00:06:10.616 --> 00:06:12.056 A:middle
component up into key value

00:06:12.056 --> 00:06:13.496 A:middle
pairs called query items.

00:06:13.496 --> 00:06:15.386 A:middle
For the query component, you can

00:06:15.386 --> 00:06:17.016 A:middle
specify a dictionary instead of

00:06:17.016 --> 00:06:19.026 A:middle
a string as its value and

00:06:19.026 --> 00:06:20.556 A:middle
pattern match individual query

00:06:20.556 --> 00:06:20.946 A:middle
items.

00:06:21.686 --> 00:06:23.636 A:middle
URLs may repeat query item names

00:06:23.706 --> 00:06:24.826 A:middle
and the operating system will

00:06:24.826 --> 00:06:26.586 A:middle
require that all instances of a

00:06:26.586 --> 00:06:28.276 A:middle
given query item name match your

00:06:28.276 --> 00:06:28.626 A:middle
pattern.

00:06:29.486 --> 00:06:31.216 A:middle
Query items with no value and

00:06:31.216 --> 00:06:32.736 A:middle
absent query items are treated

00:06:32.736 --> 00:06:34.406 A:middle
by the operating system as if

00:06:34.406 --> 00:06:35.746 A:middle
they have a value equal to the

00:06:35.746 --> 00:06:36.416 A:middle
empty string.

00:06:37.986 --> 00:06:39.306 A:middle
For a components dictionary to

00:06:39.306 --> 00:06:41.206 A:middle
match a candidate URL, all the

00:06:41.206 --> 00:06:42.866 A:middle
specified components must match.

00:06:43.466 --> 00:06:44.456 A:middle
If you don't specify a

00:06:44.456 --> 00:06:45.596 A:middle
component, the operating

00:06:45.596 --> 00:06:47.356 A:middle
system's default behavior is to

00:06:47.356 --> 00:06:48.876 A:middle
simply ignore that component.

00:06:49.456 --> 00:06:51.266 A:middle
So if, for example, your app

00:06:51.326 --> 00:06:52.576 A:middle
doesn't care about the fragment

00:06:52.576 --> 00:06:54.426 A:middle
component of a URL, you don't

00:06:54.426 --> 00:06:55.846 A:middle
need to specify it in this file.

00:06:56.556 --> 00:06:57.706 A:middle
You may have sections of your

00:06:57.706 --> 00:06:59.196 A:middle
website that are not able to be

00:06:59.196 --> 00:07:00.606 A:middle
represented in your app yet.

00:06:59.196 --> 00:07:00.606 A:middle
represented in your app yet.

00:07:01.266 --> 00:07:03.086 A:middle
You can exclude such subsections

00:07:03.086 --> 00:07:04.796 A:middle
by specifying the exclude key

00:07:05.016 --> 00:07:06.386 A:middle
with a Boolean value of true.

00:07:07.276 --> 00:07:08.826 A:middle
This key has the same behavior

00:07:08.826 --> 00:07:10.466 A:middle
as a not keyword that you used

00:07:10.466 --> 00:07:11.536 A:middle
in the old paths key.

00:07:12.056 --> 00:07:13.436 A:middle
That key word is not supported

00:07:13.436 --> 00:07:14.436 A:middle
when using the component's

00:07:14.436 --> 00:07:14.876 A:middle
dictionary.

00:07:16.626 --> 00:07:18.486 A:middle
Here we have a few examples of

00:07:18.486 --> 00:07:19.906 A:middle
URLs that we need to pattern

00:07:19.906 --> 00:07:20.286 A:middle
match.

00:07:20.726 --> 00:07:22.286 A:middle
I'm working on a meal ordering

00:07:22.286 --> 00:07:23.726 A:middle
app and I'm using universal

00:07:23.726 --> 00:07:25.436 A:middle
links to bring users into my app

00:07:25.436 --> 00:07:26.186 A:middle
from Safari.

00:07:26.616 --> 00:07:28.316 A:middle
On the left, you can see some

00:07:28.316 --> 00:07:30.146 A:middle
JSON from my server and on the

00:07:30.146 --> 00:07:31.936 A:middle
right, you can see some URLs.

00:07:32.806 --> 00:07:34.606 A:middle
First, I want to match all the

00:07:34.606 --> 00:07:36.626 A:middle
order forms on my website which

00:07:36.626 --> 00:07:38.436 A:middle
are all located on a path where

00:07:38.436 --> 00:07:39.576 A:middle
the first component can be

00:07:39.576 --> 00:07:40.076 A:middle
anything.

00:07:40.496 --> 00:07:42.086 A:middle
The second component is order

00:07:42.086 --> 00:07:43.656 A:middle
and there are no further path

00:07:43.656 --> 00:07:44.656 A:middle
components afterward.

00:07:45.806 --> 00:07:47.336 A:middle
This pattern will match a URL

00:07:47.336 --> 00:07:48.786 A:middle
such as these two on the right.

00:07:49.136 --> 00:07:49.856 A:middle
Time for lunch.

00:07:51.396 --> 00:07:52.746 A:middle
Next, I know a lot of my

00:07:52.746 --> 00:07:54.126 A:middle
customers are going to want to

00:07:54.126 --> 00:07:56.026 A:middle
put cheese on their tacos so I'm

00:07:56.026 --> 00:07:57.726 A:middle
going to match any URL where the

00:07:57.726 --> 00:07:59.246 A:middle
path starts with the path

00:07:59.246 --> 00:08:01.866 A:middle
component taco and where a query

00:07:59.246 --> 00:08:01.866 A:middle
component taco and where a query

00:08:01.866 --> 00:08:03.986 A:middle
item named cheese is specified.

00:08:04.626 --> 00:08:05.916 A:middle
You'll notice that I specify a

00:08:05.916 --> 00:08:07.946 A:middle
question mark and an asterisk as

00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:09.286 A:middle
the pattern from the query items

00:08:09.286 --> 00:08:09.676 A:middle
value.

00:08:09.966 --> 00:08:12.046 A:middle
A pattern consisting of a single

00:08:12.046 --> 00:08:13.696 A:middle
asterisk matches any string,

00:08:13.826 --> 00:08:15.066 A:middle
including the empty string.

